19/05/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Tomislav Nikolic, the presidential candidate of the Serbian Radical Party, continues to lead in opinion polls as next month's election approaches.
Results of a survey by the Marten Board International rating agency were released Tuesday (18 May).
The survey found that Nikolic would get 30.8 per cent of the vote, a slight increase from previous polls.
Democratic Party candidate Boris Tadic came in second with 22.1 per cent support, also registering a slight increase.
The governing coalition's candidate, Dragan Marsicanin, was third with 18.6 per cent.
Bogoljub Karic, an independent latecomer, got 11.2 per cent.
(B92, Tanjug - 18/05/04)
